# ZK Identity Authentication System

A privacy-preserving authentication protocol using zk-SNARKs on Ethereum.

## Architecture

- Circom circuits for Merkle inclusion proofs
- Groth16 proof generation using snarkjs
- Poseidon-based identity commitments
- Solidity verifier contract
- Replay protection via nullifiers

## Stack

- Circom
- snarkjs
- Solidity
- Hardhat
- Poseidon hash
- Groth16 zk-SNARK

## Features

- Anonymous authentication
- Merkle tree membership proof
- Replay protection with nullifiers
- On-chain proof verification

## Workflow

1. User generates identity (nullifier + trapdoor)
2. Commitment inserted into Merkle tree
3. Client generates zk-proof locally
4. Proof verified on-chain

